theorem P3_implies_closure_interior_closure_eq_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 (A : Set X) →
      closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = closure A := by
  intro hP3
  -- `closure (interior (closure A))` is always contained in `closure A`.
  have h₁ :
      closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono
      (interior_subset : interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A)
  -- Conversely, `P3` gives `A ⊆ interior (closure A)`, hence the closures are ordered the other way.
  have h₂ :
      closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
    closure_mono
      (hP3 : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior (closure A))
  -- Combine the two inclusions to obtain equality.
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem interior_closure_interior_subset_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
  exact interior_mono (closure_mono (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A))

theorem interior_closure_inter_interior_subset
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (closure ((A ∩ interior B) : Set X)) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
  -- `A ∩ interior B` is contained in `A`.
  have hSub : (A ∩ interior B : Set X) ⊆ A := by
    intro x hx
    exact hx.1
  -- Therefore, the closure of `A ∩ interior B` is contained in the closure of `A`.
  have hClSub : closure (A ∩ interior B : Set X) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono hSub
  -- Applying monotonicity of `interior` yields the desired inclusion.
  exact interior_mono hClSub
